Thingworx Guide
1
Open your browser and navigate to: "https://IP_Data_Collector/". You can also use
the a4conf icon on the Data Collector desktop.
2
Click "Data-Sender" within the main menu.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 2
3
Select "Thingworx".
4
Enter the server name in the "Server" field.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 3
5
Enter the Appkey in the "Appkey" field. You can click the "eye" icon to the right to
see the Appkey in clear text.
6
Move to "Remote Things".
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 4
7
Open the drop-down menu to show all the enabled IoT Gateway for Thingworx.
8
Choose from all available options.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 5
9
Click the "add" button to the right of the drop-down menu to add the selected IoT
Gateway to the table below. This means that the tags contained in these IoT
Gateways will be sent on ThingWorx to the thing identified as "Remote Thing
Name."
10
You can also manually add a new Remote Thing to the table with the "+" icon.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 6
11
Fill in Remote Things details and click the "Ok" button to add the new item to the
table.
12
You can now click the "Save" button.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 7
13
Move to "Manage IoT Gateways".
14
Enable/Disable each IoT Gateway for Thingworx by selecting the checkbox on the
right.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 8
15
Move to "Agent Logs".
16
Click the "Test connection" button to test the connection.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 9
17
After waiting for feedback from the page you can click on the configured remote
things to get a detail on each of them.
18
Select the "Thingworx service status" to disable the Thingworx service. After this
operation you will be directed to the "Data Sender" page.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 10
19
Select the "Thingworx agent disabled" checkbox to enable Thingworx service
again.
20
You can now return to the Thingworx page.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 11
21
Click the "Apply" button to apply the new configurations.
22
Select the required option from "Thingworx service commands" to start, stop or
restart the Thingworx service.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 12
23
Select the "Reboot Data Sender" checkbox to reboot the Data Sender. Click the
"Apply" button to start the reboot.
